00:04:07.554 --> 00:04:08.592
- [Voiceover] Exactly.

00:04:08.592 --> 00:04:10.840
- [Voiceover] And so when you order online

00:04:10.840 --> 00:04:12.776
or wherever that you
want a certain primer,

00:04:12.776 --> 00:04:15.024
you're going to pick the
sequence of that primer

00:04:15.024 --> 00:04:16.955
to be specific to the
regions you want to copy.

00:04:16.955 --> 00:04:18.843
- [Voiceover] Exactly.
That's super important.

00:04:18.843 --> 00:04:21.099
- [Voiceover] Okay. And so
when you cool it back down,

00:04:21.099 --> 00:04:22.842
the primer attaches,

00:04:22.842 --> 00:04:25.456
and then you heat it back up,

00:04:25.456 --> 00:04:27.667
not quite to the 96 degrees Celsius,

00:04:27.667 --> 00:04:29.384
but to the 72 degrees Celsius,

00:04:29.384 --> 00:04:31.435
where you extend those.

00:04:31.435 --> 00:04:32.738
And I'm assuming since it's called

00:04:32.738 --> 00:04:34.618
Polymerase Chain Reaction,

00:04:34.618 --> 00:04:36.819
