00:04:56.074 --> 00:04:58.684
- [Voiceover] So you actually
need a special polymerase,

00:04:58.684 --> 00:05:00.074
because you need one that is going

00:05:00.074 --> 00:05:01.269
to be pretty heat-resistant,

00:05:01.269 --> 00:05:02.442
so as you were mentioning,

00:05:02.442 --> 00:05:04.170
even the cool step of this process

00:05:04.170 --> 00:05:05.650
is not something that your body

00:05:05.650 --> 00:05:07.658
would want to be hanging out in.

00:05:07.658 --> 00:05:09.654
So the polymerase is actually from

00:05:09.654 --> 00:05:12.402
a really heat-tolerant micro-organism.

00:05:12.402 --> 00:05:14.765
- [Voiceover] And what is that?

00:05:14.765 --> 00:05:16.244
It's called a taq polymerase?

00:05:16.244 --> 00:05:18.826
- [Voiceover] It's thermophilus
aquaticus, I think?

00:05:18.826 --> 00:05:20.164
Makes quite a mouthful.

00:05:20.164 --> 00:05:23.215
- [Voiceover] And they
found it at heated vents,

00:05:23.215 --> 00:05:26.586
this organism that is able to
stand these high temperatures.

00:05:26.586 --> 00:05:30.010
But that I guess leads
